fields.name: PccRules
fields.description: The set of data flow policy rules that make up this service.

fields.name: ServicePrecedence
fields.description: A precedence value that is used to decide between services when identifying the QoS values to use for a particular SIM. A lower value means a higher priority. This value should be unique among all services configured in the mobile network.

fields.name: ServiceQosPolicy
fields.description: The QoS policy to use for packets matching this service. This can be overridden for particular flows using the ruleQosPolicy field in a PccRuleConfiguration. If this field is null then the UE's SIM policy will define the QoS settings.
